sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K136009
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: fliL promoter followed by its natural RBS
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Promoter of fliL gene from E. coli flagella
fliL is a class 2 gene that is part of the construction of the flagella ( Ordering Genes in a Flagella Pathway by Analysis of Expression Kinetics from Living Bacteria - S. Kalir, J. McClure, K. Pabbaraju, C. Southward, M. Ronen, S. Leibler, M. G. Surette, U. Alon, ).
Its promoter is consitutively repressed.
It is activated by flhD4C2 and by fliA with different forces ( Using a Quantitative Blueprint to Reprogram the Dynamics of the Flagella Gene Network - Shiraz Kalir and Uri Alon ).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kok-Phen YAN
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part comes from the genome of E.coli K12 strain MG1655.
